{"items":[{"id":"22c43df0-9d9e-4906-9ec0-0b22b5bfa711","text":"The words 'tighten' and 'spot' are forbidden in posts; instead, specific verbs like 'identify', 'reduce', 'cap', or 'limit' should be used. | To use more specific and actionable language.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.958929+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.958929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"spot, tighten","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_bafe8709-ad0c-4cbd-bf72-a94af7f68171_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"f38f2eaf-16c9-490d-bf0b-f01998745787","text":"Maintain a confident and direct tone in marketing posts, avoiding corporate jargon, buzzwords, and specific terms like 'just', 'thrilled', 'excited', 'delighted', 'game-changer', 'revolutionary', 'leverage', 'synergy', 'tighten', and 'spot'. When referring to tightening or spotting, use specific verbs like 'identify', 'reduce', 'cap', or 'limit'.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.819595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.958929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":4,"tags":[]},{"id":"b3cf5feb-911e-4070-9bd8-080e995ccf18","text":"Write all numbers in posts using digits; do not spell them out.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.948929+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.948929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"2060c2ca-5e83-4cdc-9c7a-b46389604aca","text":"All numbers in posts must be written using digits, never spelled out.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.948929+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.948929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"numbers","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_bafe8709-ad0c-4cbd-bf72-a94af7f68171_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"94d6efa6-6f12-4b3f-b8d5-11f7287ba298","text":"When listing two or more speakers in posts, use their actual names and titles when known, rather than role-only labels like 'our VP of Product'.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.938929+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.938929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"efb180ca-2afd-41ad-ae95-1917084d14ae","text":"When listing two or more speakers in posts, use their actual names and titles when known, and do not refer to them by role-only labels like 'our VP of Product'.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.938929+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.938929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"speakers","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_bafe8709-ad0c-4cbd-bf72-a94af7f68171_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"fb5dd1e3-af5b-4b35-94e6-ef9c56531a74","text":"For webinar/event posts, place the date and time on its own line, separate from the body, using the format 'Tuesday Apr 14, 2pm ET'.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.928929+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.928929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"c1ea7f50-3e79-4bdb-8153-df294895dd2b","text":"For webinar/event posts, the date and time should be on its own line, separate from the body, using the format 'Tuesday Apr 14, 2pm ET' for scannability. | To ensure scannability of the date and time.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.928929+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:16:13.928929+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"webinar/event posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_bafe8709-ad0c-4cbd-bf72-a94af7f68171_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"2ce19fd5-615a-4d46-8a14-424a0cb27bb0","text":"Marketing posts must never explicitly thank people; instead, they should name what the community did (e.g., broke it, improved it, opened PRs, filed issues).","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.325255+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.325255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"b9bd0890-6d02-4599-b637-de01e132bea9","text":"Marketing posts must never explicitly thank people; instead, they should name what the community did (e.g., broke it, improved it, opened PRs, filed issues).","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.325255+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.325255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"community, marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d382e1ed-f99e-4976-84b0-af1fddd54202_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"e5ffd4bf-1794-45c9-a520-d69dc9e4cd45","text":"For milestone marketing posts (stars, signups, downloads, ARR, customers), the first line must lead with a provocative claim about what the milestone means for the audience, without mentioning the metric, and the metric should be placed in the second sentence as proof of this claim.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.305255+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.315255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"2bb73ec1-cf66-411a-925b-34b912800020","text":"For milestone marketing posts, the metric should be placed in the second sentence as proof of the provocative claim.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.315255+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.315255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"milestone marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d382e1ed-f99e-4976-84b0-af1fddd54202_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"92d24347-c90c-484a-9d6b-e1b16a59fba1","text":"For milestone marketing posts (stars, signups, downloads, ARR, customers), the first line must lead with a provocative claim about what the milestone means for the audience, without mentioning the metric.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.305255+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.305255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"milestone marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d382e1ed-f99e-4976-84b0-af1fddd54202_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"0ba85e9d-784a-431d-adbe-08906efe01ec","text":"Marketing posts must never use the word 'just'.","context":"marketing writing rules","date":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.295255+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:15:21.295255+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d382e1ed-f99e-4976-84b0-af1fddd54202_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"979e4a5a-dab0-40b9-88d1-2a8d1af4c146","text":"New product or feature announcements must include a concrete metric or outcome in the second sentence and should avoid vague benefits.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.871922+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.881922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"23fd2e85-0576-47f1-919f-e393ea28b3c8","text":"New product or feature announcements should avoid vague benefits.","context":"marketing writing corrections","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.881922+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.881922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"feature announcements, vague benefits, product announcements","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d90a41b8-9ee3-4527-9634-51f17239d9e4_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"be3d151d-3b3f-4efa-8350-b61b4186e1d8","text":"New product or feature announcements must include a concrete metric or outcome in the second sentence.","context":"marketing writing corrections","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.871922+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.871922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"metric, outcome, product announcements, feature announcements","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d90a41b8-9ee3-4527-9634-51f17239d9e4_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"02d2847d-81a7-4554-84dd-9b8e70dae221","text":"The correct order for elements in marketing posts is body, followed by the signature, and then the closing question, which must appear on its own line after the signature.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.851922+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.861922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"8456b58c-8d74-4e59-953d-2b6c2bc74dcd","text":"The correct order for elements in marketing posts is body -> signature -> question.","context":"marketing writing corrections","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.861922+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.861922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"body, question, signature, marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d90a41b8-9ee3-4527-9634-51f17239d9e4_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"259e38d8-5a70-4569-b6d4-aeccfb31bcb4","text":"The closing question in marketing posts must appear on its own line after the signature.","context":"marketing writing corrections","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.851922+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.851922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts, signature, closing question","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d90a41b8-9ee3-4527-9634-51f17239d9e4_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"dee32e2b-bf2d-4ca1-9831-d274716fee3b","text":"All future marketing posts must have the sign-off \"— the team\" on its own line at the very end, preceded by a blank line.","context":"marketing writing corrections","date":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.841922+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.841922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts, sign-off","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_d90a41b8-9ee3-4527-9634-51f17239d9e4_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"c23a4e74-ae13-44cd-b003-f67b21338ae2","text":"Marketing posts must be signed off as '— the team' on its own line at the very end, preceded by a blank line, and avoid using 'I' or 'we'.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.919595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:13:20.841922+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":2,"tags":[]},{"id":"709acf24-1f6e-409e-b7a3-a590ee8d7361","text":"Marketing posts must conclude with a single open-ended question to encourage engagement.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.939595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.939595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"3554382a-8247-4271-9d55-d731ac6d8379","text":"Marketing posts must always conclude with a single open-ended question to encourage engagement.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.939595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.939595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"4116a8e7-8db4-47fb-89c0-b7ac7941abf3","text":"Hashtags are forbidden in marketing posts.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.929595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.929595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"57f8ca2c-084f-4b0d-b207-0a5230f42a57","text":"Hashtags are forbidden in marketing posts.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.929595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.929595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts, hashtags","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"86c8babd-bf32-407c-b5aa-32ba4d95d209","text":"Posts should be signed as 'the team' and never use 'I' or 'we'.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.919595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.919595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"51876f32-1958-43a0-9d2a-eeb79f3ded67","text":"The use of specific words such as 'thrilled', 'excited', 'delighted', 'game-changer', 'revolutionary', 'leverage', and 'synergy' is banned in marketing posts.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.909595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.909595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"992cfbf7-2cda-4c34-9036-e8b3ade62c97","text":"Emojis are forbidden in marketing posts.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.899595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.899595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"773bbcf9-59ae-4d85-b1cb-eeb031190583","text":"Emojis are forbidden in marketing posts.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.899595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.899595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts, emojis","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"e6a922bd-75a8-43b7-a517-53322fb0d486","text":"Start marketing posts by highlighting the user benefit or the importance of the topic, rather than with a direct announcement.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.889595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.889595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"98305ab3-6ba4-4e51-8cc7-cc3735ce13f0","text":"Marketing posts should lead with the user benefit or why the topic matters, rather than the announcement itself.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.889595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.889595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"aca5a823-ce70-430f-b9d5-e37d90592748","text":"Avoid long-winded introductions in marketing posts.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.879595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.879595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"56bc0f1d-4c3e-4676-bada-6e33a221f0d2","text":"Marketing posts should avoid long-winded introductions.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.879595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.879595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"ff6d7254-f050-45a1-af5a-053349f67d75","text":"Structure LinkedIn posts with a maximum of 4 short paragraphs.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.869595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.869595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"3c0e2050-5898-4675-b860-1ce761f8cbe7","text":"LinkedIn posts must be structured with a maximum of 4 short paragraphs.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.869595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.869595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"LinkedIn posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"872779e8-5ba8-4b2a-ae93-d85bc89d5c26","text":"Limit LinkedIn posts to a maximum of 600 characters.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.859595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.859595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"233cf16a-33aa-4d0f-9877-5dec4d1059eb","text":"LinkedIn posts must have a maximum length of 600 characters.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.859595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.859595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"LinkedIn posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"556fb4ea-7c73-4231-852f-a195940b47d7","text":"Do not simplify content for the technical leader audience; maintain a high level of technical detail.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.849595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.849595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"b9b0bdf7-b431-4d90-ac1e-60dd7985c2e3","text":"Content for marketing posts should not be dumbed down for the technical leader audience.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.849595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.849595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"technical leader audience, marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"17bdd6c2-9471-4614-bc20-a169c9e5aae1","text":"Target marketing posts towards technical leaders, such as CTOs, VPs of Engineering, and staff-plus engineers.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.839595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.839595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"0e7404b8-5da7-454e-a345-35a25f9d7757","text":"The target audience for marketing posts is technical leaders, including CTOs, VPs of Engineering, and staff-plus engineers.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.839595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.839595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"VPs of Engineering, staff-plus engineers, CTOs, technical leaders","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"581bdeb3-66e3-42a6-b8ff-be66336eba98","text":"Ensure marketing posts sound conversational and human, not like a formal press release.","context":"","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.829595+00:00","fact_type":"observation","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.829595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"","chunk_id":null,"proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"dc412215-b1e5-470e-8af3-306148c3f7e8","text":"Marketing posts should sound like a smart human, not a press release.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.829595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.829595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]},{"id":"cac63c1e-d6f4-4834-b5ed-27ddbe665a33","text":"The tone for marketing posts should be confident and direct, avoiding corporate or buzzwordy language.","context":"marketing writing guidelines","date":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.819595+00:00","fact_type":"world","mentioned_at":"2026-04-09T20:10:32.819595+00:00","occurred_start":null,"occurred_end":null,"entities":"marketing posts","chunk_id":"marketing-manager_33f8c674-153e-4de5-bc9a-b6314471a35c_0","proof_count":1,"tags":[]}],"total":45,"limit":50,"offset":0}